BORDER:::
-> border-style: solid;
-> border-width: 2px;
-> border-color: brown;
-> border-radius: 5px; ... curve the edgess...
   even one corner can also be done...see the palet...
-> width:250px; .. kitna left-right mai bada hoga...
-> height:200px ... kitna top-bottom mai bda hogaa...
-> width and height wont apply on inline elements ...they depend only on content inside them..  
-> SHORT HAND NOTATION:::: border:solid green 5px;

BOX MODEL:::
-> Hamare pas agar koi bhi shape ka text, image kuch bhi ho...browser usse rectangle shape mai hi render karega / display karegaa...
-> 4parts:- content..padding..border..margin
SEE PHOTO IN THIS FOLDER..
-> PADDING... layer existing between border and content...on increasing padding(in px) ..gap between content and border increases...
-> MARGIN... pura pura move hoga with border..leaving space ...
-> Padding Margin can be done individually on each side only...
SHORT HAND::: padding:  top right bottom left (in px)
              padding: y axis  x axis (in px)

UNIVERSAL SELECTOR:::
-> * { padding : 0px ;
       border-width : 0px; }
Taki universally har tag/element mai lag jayeee...

box-sizing : border-box;
The box-sizing property allows us to include the padding and border in an element's total width and height.
If you set box-sizing: border-box; on an element, padding, and border are included in the width and height..

